						bhaginiya</lem>
            <rdg source="bib:Vogeld">sodarābhaginiya</rdg>
            <note>The emendation is supported by EIAD <ref target="DHARMA_INSEIAD00005.xml">5</ref>, l. 5 <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">sodaraya
						bhaginiya</foreign>.</note>
          </app>
          <app loc="5">
            <lem>haṁmas<supplied reason="omitted">i</supplied>riya</lem>
            <note>We suspect the engraver started writing a <foreign>si</foreign>, but stopped after the
						first short horizontal stroke.</note>
          </app>
          <app loc="7">
            <lem>°atānaṁ</lem>
            <rdg source="bib:Vogeld">°atanaṁ</rdg>
            <note>It is perhaps not necessary to emend <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">°atano</foreign>, as proposed by Vogel in his n. 6, because <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">°atānaṁ</foreign> can be a gen. pl. form and confusion of number is not unusual. The parallel passage in EIAD <ref target="DHARMA_INSEIAD00005.xml">5</ref>, l. 7, which mentions the same mother Hammasirī, here has <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">°atane</foreign>.</note>
          </app>
          <app loc="7">
            <lem>bhaṁkhaṁ</lem>
            <note>Emend <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">khaṁbhaṁ</foreign>,
						as proposed by Vogel in his n. 7.</note>
          </app>
          <app loc="8">
            <lem>d<supplied reason="omitted">i</supplied>va</lem>
            <rdg source="bib:Vogeld">dāva</rdg>
            <note>The first akṣara is clearly <foreign>da</foreign>. Vogel emends to <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">diva</foreign>.</note>
          </app>
        </listApp>
